	<div class="row">
		<div class="col-md-12">
			<div id="ctl00_ctl00_MainContentPlaceHolder_PageContentPlaceHolder_PageContentPlaceHolder_RichHtmlField1_label" style='display:none'></div><div id="ctl00_ctl00_MainContentPlaceHolder_PageContentPlaceHolder_PageContentPlaceHolder_RichHtmlField1__ControlWrapper_OregonRichHtmlField" class="ms-rtestate-field" style="display:inline" ><h5 class="ms-rteElement-Heading5" style="font-family&#58;calibri, arial, sans-serif;color&#58;#282828;text-align&#58;center;"> 
   <span style="font-weight&#58;700;color&#58;inherit;font-family&#58;inherit;font-size&#58;1.5rem;">
      <img src="/transparency/Priority%20Icons/agreement.png" alt="" style="margin&#58;5px;width&#58;100px;height&#58;103px;" /></span></h5><h3 class="ms-rteElement-Heading3" style="text-align&#58;center;">State Agency Contract and Procurement<br></h3><h4 class="ms-rteElement-Heading4" style="text-align&#58;center;">Contract reporting, price agreements,&#160;bid process, OregonBuys and related resources.<br></h4><p></p><div style="text-align&#58;center;">
   <img src="/transparency/PublishingImages/1123x375-seal-description-contracts.jpg" alt="" style="margin&#58;5px;width&#58;1200px;height&#58;400px;" />&#160;<br></div><blockquote style="margin&#58;0px 0px 0px 40px;border&#58;none;padding&#58;0px;"><h5 class="ms-rteElement-Heading5">The&#160;<a href="/das/procurement/pages/index.aspx">Department of Administrative State Procurment Services(SPS)</a>&#160;is the central authority for state agency purchasing, managing, and contracting for goods and services. It provides leadership, training, and policy guidance, and utilizes the 
      <a href="https&#58;//oregonbuys.gov/bso/">
         OregonBuys </a>system for bidding. DAS PS ensures compliance with state contracting laws. the central procurement authority for state agencies that are subject to DAS authority.&#160;Examples include the Oregon Lottery, Judicial Department, and the Oregon Department of Transportation.<br></h5><h5 class="ms-rteElement-Heading5">The state Purchases and Contracts Dashboard, related&#160;resources and links can be found below.<br></h5><p></p><div style="text-align&#58;center;"></div><div class="ms-rtestate-read ms-rte-wpbox"><div class="ms-rtestate-notify  ms-rtestate-read a206e8c4-b3a6-4afb-8344-5c8c29c06ce1" id="div_a206e8c4-b3a6-4afb-8344-5c8c29c06ce1" unselectable="on"><div id="MSOZoneCell_WebPartctl00_ctl00_ctl40_g_a206e8c4_b3a6_4afb_8344_5c8c29c06ce1" class="s4-wpcell-plain ms-webpartzone-cell ms-webpart-cell-vertical-inline-table ms-webpart-cell-vertical ms-fullWidth ">
	<div class="ms-webpart-chrome ms-webpart-chrome-vertical ms-webpart-chrome-fullWidth ">
	<div    id="WebPartctl00_ctl00_ctl40_g_a206e8c4_b3a6_4afb_8344_5c8c29c06ce1"  class="ms-WPBody noindex "   allowExport="false" style="" ><div id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl40_g_a206e8c4_b3a6_4afb_8344_5c8c29c06ce1">
		<DIV class="ms-rte-embedcode ms-rte-embedwp"><iframe title="State Contracts Multi-Year Report 2026" width="1250" height="800" src="https://app.powerbigov.us/view?r=eyJrIjoiMWEyYjgyODMtNWU1Yi00NjEzLWI4ZjUtZWVmMjYwNTM1NTYyIiwidCI6ImFhM2Y2OTMyLWZhN2MtNDdiNC1hMGNlLWE1OThjYWQxNjFjZiJ9" frameborder="0" allowFullScreen="true"></iframe></DIV>
	</div><div class="ms-clear"></div></div>
</div>
</div></div><div id="vid_a206e8c4-b3a6-4afb-8344-5c8c29c06ce1" unselectable="on" style="display&#58;none;"></div></div><br></blockquote></div>
